text: First time visiting. Well ventilated and litted canteen in tuas area. Variety of food is available, muslim, non-muslim and  vegetarian. Washroom available on site. Car Parks available at roadside.

Standard coffeeshop. Clean but with some occasional flies. Feels hot - can't feel breeze from ceiling fan. Food selection is limited but it's okay for a quick meal. Parking is available but need to wait for parking at peak times.
The noodles comes in quite a large portion. The soup was a little oily because of the fried garlic put inside. The coffee here needs improvement.

Claypot curry chicken is very tasty, servicing is big (one full chicken drumstick), uncle auntie are very friendly as well.
Must try!
It is a convenient food centre in the industrial area. Ample car park space.  Have lost a few food stalls after covid but still popular.
